landic people of Spanish descent|Baltasar Kormakur]]\n[[Category:People from Reykjav\u00edk|Baltasar Kormakur]]\n[[Category:Icelandic male film actors|Baltasar Kormakur]]\n[[Category:20th-century Icelandic people|Baltasar Kormakur]]\n[[Category:Icelandic people with family names|Baltasar Kormakur]]\n", "name_user": "89.17.157.25", "label": "vandal", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Baltasar_Korm%C3%A1kur"}
{"title_page": "Kataoka Ainosuke VI", "text_new": "{{short description|Japanese kabuki actor|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name             = Kataoka Ainosuke VI\n| image            = http://wiki.d-addicts.com/File:Kataoka_Ainosuke.jpg \n| caption          = \n| native_name      = \u516d\u4ee3\u76ee \u7247\u5ca1 \u611b\u4e4b\u52a9\n| native_name_lang = ja\n| birth_name       = {{nihongo|Hiroyuki Yamamoto|\u5c71\u5143 \u5bdb\u4e4b|Yamamoto Hiroyuki}}\n| birth_date       = {{Birth date and age|1972|3|4}}\n| birth_place      = [[Sakai, Osaka]], Japan\n| death_date       =\n| death_place      = \n| resting_place    = \n| residence        = Tokyo, Japan\n| nationality      = Japanese\n| education        = \n| occupation       = Actor\n| years_active     = 1981\u2013present \n| agent            = \n| known_for        = \n| home_town        = \n| height           = 172 cm \n| weight           = 64 kg\n| awards           = \n| website          = {{official website|http://ameblo.jp/6ainosuke/}}\n| alias            = \n| spouse           = {{marriage|[[Norika Fujiwara]]|2016}}\n}}\n{{nihongo|'''Kataoka Ainosuke VI'''|\u516d\u4ee3\u76ee \u7247\u5ca1 \u611b\u4e4b\u52a9|Rokudaime Kataoka Ainosuke|born March 4, 1972, in [[Sakai, Osaka]], Japan}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kabuki.ne.jp/meikandb/meikan/actor/12|title=\u6b4c\u821e\u4f0e\u4ff3\u512a\u540d\u9451 \u73fe\u5728\u306e\u4ff3\u512a\u7bc7 / \u7247\u5ca1\u611b\u4e4b\u52a9\uff08\u516d\u4ee3\u76ee\uff09|language=ja|publisher=Kabuki on the Web|accessdate=March 3, 2016}}</ref> is a Japanese [[kabuki]] actor. His ''[[yag\u014d]]'' is ''matsushimaya''. His ''[[Mon (emblem)|mon]]'' is the ''Oikake Go-mai Ich\u014d''. His current stage name is Ainosuke Kataoka.\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Kabuki===\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Title\n! Notes\n|-\n| ''Sh\u014dchiku \u014ckabuki'' ||\n|-\n| ''Heisei Wakash\u016b Kabuki'' ||\n|-\n| ''Asakusa Kabuki'' ||\n|-\n| ''Hanagata Kabuki'' ||\n|-\n| ''Mitsukoshi Kabuki'' ||\n|-\n| ''Eirak